Usually you put logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG) at the start of every program to see the log.

It's easy to forget this though.

@tqchen @antinucleon Maybe we should put logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG) into mxnet's init?

Maybe put all the logger default value of all methods to be `None`, and then have a internal `mxnet.logging` module defining some method like

``` python
def get_logger(logger):
    if logger is None:
        # construct or re-use some global default logger
    else:
        return logger
```
